{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"AC reconciliation (design decision, recorded not silent): AC1 originally specified an Inspect AI Task assembly behind the eval extra via guard_import. During implementation that proved a poor fit — our 'model call' is a whole tool-using agentic op (verify_completion/review_ticket/scan_spec), which does not map onto Inspect's single-completion solver/scorer model; wrapping it would add a dependency and an impedance mismatch for no gain. Decision: run_eval is a NATIVE loop over the eval solver, reusing the already-tested discipline primitives (at_least(k)/coverage/kappa/to_junit/the scorer registry), emitting JUnit for promptfoo/CI. The live runner is gated by the agents extra (the agentic ops' pydantic_ai backend), not the eval extra. Rationale is documented in eval.py (the run_eval section comment). AC1 (here), the WS-EVAL story, and the epic AC have been updated to match this decision. Substance delivered: run_eval runs a real live eval (validated by a live single-case smoke), regression-gating all dataset-bearing specs; AC3 cost rails (max_cases ceiling + pip cache + sequential exec) added."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782586732024686001,"uuid":"b29303dd-6ae9-423d-8c3b-62b1550ee87d"}